text: N-Ethyltryptamine (NET), or merely ethyltryptamine, is a tryptamine that is structurally related to N-methyltryptamine (NMT) and the psychedelic drugs N,N-dimethyltryptamine (DMT) and N,N-diethyltryptamine (DET).NET Entry in TIHKAL == See also == * N-Methyltryptamine (NMT) * N,N,-Dimethyltryptamine (DMT) == References == Category:Tryptamines Category:Serotonin receptor agonists
title: N-Ethyltryptamine
